The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 03 November is 301,612 (34,762.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 29 October, there were 531 new confirmed cases (61.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 22 October, there were 852 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 38% (321 fewer cases).
